Package: bootabc
Title: Bootstrap Experiment Confidence Intervals
Version: 0.9.5
Authors@R: 
    person("First", "Last", , "first.last@example.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Computes bootstrap confidence intervals for key performance
    indicators (KPIs) measured in online controlled experiments (A/B tests),
    where data is aggregated to one row per customer or visitor. Supports
    compound KPIs defined as ratios of sums, such as spend per active day, and
    comparisons between experiment variants. Resampling runs through a streaming
    'C++' kernel so that large experiments remain tractable. Variance can be
    reduced using pre-experiment data via the CUPED method of
    Deng, Xu, Kohavi and Walker (2013) <doi:10.1145/2433396.2433413>.
